I think the other combinations may also be `URi`, `URI`, `uRi`, `uRI`, `urI`?
Should bmcweb has its own `bmcweb::iends_with()`?

URI is already handled.

The rest are badly formed naming conventions in Redfish, so they're not supported.   I did check, there are no property names in the schema that use capitalization like you have.
I think it should be good enough to check those - uri, Uri, and URI, and the others can be treated as errors.
